author: COMSOL
description:
This example demonstrates how to calculate effective transport properties of a heterogeneous 3D geometry of a nickel manganese cobalt (NMC) electrode.

The effective parameters are then used to create a representative homogenized 1D model of the NMC electrode. By homogenizing, memory requirements and computational times are reduced by orders of magnitude.
